               <head>Anis al-talibin of Salah Bukhari</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Anīs al-ṭālibīn vaʿdat al-sālikīn by Ṣalāḥ ibn Mubārak al-Bukhārī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_957-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f5549">Ṣalāḥ ibn Mubārak al-Bukhārī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f5549">صلاح ابن مبارك البخارى </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7986">Anīs al-ṭālibīn vaʿdat al-sālikīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_7986">نيس الطّالبين وعدة السّالكين</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on the biographies of early Naqshbandī Sufis, especially <persName key="viaf_6835087" role="subject">Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad Bukhārī the Naqshband</persName> (d. 791/1388), entitled <title>Anīs al-ṭālibīn [va] vaʿdat al-sālikīn</title>, compiled after having consultation with friends and successors of Bahāʾ al-Dīn Naqshband at the request of <persName key="person_f7268" role="oth">Mawlānā Ḥusām al-Dīn Khvājah Yūsuf</persName> (d. 791/1389) who descended from <persName key="person_f7266" role="oth">Mawlānā Ḥāfiẓ al-Dīn Kabīr Bukhārī</persName>, by the author <persName key="person_f5549" role="aut com">Ṣalāḥ ibn Mubārak al-Bukhārī</persName>, then in the service of <persName key="person_f7221" role="pat crr">Khvājah ʿAlāʾ al-Dīn known as ʿAṭṭār</persName> (who also corrected the work). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into four qism. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 161v): completed by <persName key="person_f7394" role="scr">Muḥammad Riz̤āʾ ibn Ḥājī ibn ʿAlī</persName>, on the morning of Saturday, 10 Jumādá al-S̲ānī 1041/3 January 1632, for <persName key="person_f7312" role="pat">Mīrzā Muḥammad Liqāʾ</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Neat and minute scribal nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                        <p>Marginal corrections and annotations. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios cropped. 
</p>
                        <p>Outermost folios heavily damaged by wormholes. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacks original binding. Present covers include 1) a delaminating and worm-eaten binding with brown leather outside, and doublures ornamented with blind tooled medallions; 2) loose folded paper wrapper (EIC legislation for 1850, torn and stained, undated watermarked (seated Britannia or Minerva in crowned oval). 
</p>
                        <p>Condition fragile. 
</p>
                     </note>
